methods.readExternalStreaming:
Alternative to Externalizable.readExternal(ObjectInput) for use when a series of tuples of
 the same type with the same element types are being read in iterative fashion.
 Primitive elements should be read with their primitive read methods (e.g. DataInput.readInt()).
 Object elements are preceded by a boolean, true if null, false otherwise. The first non-null value for a given
 Object element is then preceded by the name of the class. All non-null values are then read with a reader
 method from SerializationUtils.getReader(Class, ObjectInput), cached in cachedReaders.

:param in: java.io.ObjectInput
:param cachedReaders: gnu.trove.map.TIntObjectMap<io.deephaven.db.util.serialization.SerializationUtils.Reader>
